The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems on weighted graphs, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on developing algorithms with improved time complexity suggests that cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CG and cs.NA. The mention of interior-point methods and preconditioning techniques also suggests a connection to optimization and machine learning, hence cs.LG is a possible category as well.
